#week-title("Three", "Salt — The Purified Body")

=== Core Teaching

The Salt is the body of the herb, purified by fire to its mineral essence. The
Salt of each plant is unique and specific — it contains the fixed mineral
character of that particular plant. This is why salts must not be intermixed
across kingdoms; each kingdom operates at a distinct vibratory rate.

Record the weight and appearance of your Salt at each stage in your laboratory
journal. The transition from black carbon to light grey is the first evidence of
the *Nigredo* giving way to the *Albedo*.

=== Topics This Week

- Salt as the unique mineral signature of the plant
- Recording weights: tracking the loss of the gross and recovery of the subtle
- Diagnostic check: recognizing glazed vs. purified salt

#inner-work[
  *The Role of the Practitioner*

  The tradition is explicit: an impure operator produces an impure preparation.
  The practitioner who does not perform their own personal calcination brings
  impurities into the laboratory work itself.

  Reflect on your descending waking dreams. What "primitive tendencies" or
  erroneous beliefs have you identified? Do not judge them — simply observe them
  as you observe the ash in your crucible.
]

